gomodel:SYNGO_2111  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3B/C Rich2 KD (shRNA) decreases transferrin-rhodamine recycling in neurons and COS-7 cells [fluorescent pulse-chase].\n\nFig.3D Rich2 promotes recycling of GFP-tagged AMPARs to the surface of hipp neurons\n\nFig.4/5 Rich2 activity is needed for spine enlargement induced by chemical LTP and increase of synaptic currents, and increase of surface levels of synaptic AMPARs [fixed tissue] (NMDAR activation) [Rich2 KD, OE Rich2 mutant proteins]\n\n11/12/2017 Pim\n- Since ARHGAP44 / Rich2 is a regulator of signaling and not a transporting protein itself I have selected the \"regulates...\" variant of the term.. Experimental description: \"Neuronal hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryos of either sex of E-17 Swiss mice and grown in Neurobasal medium supplemented with B27 and 10% fetal bovine serum (FBS).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2111" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

